**“Superman: The Left of the Hummingbird,” by Bef (Bernardo Fernández) (Mexico)**

When Clark Kent visits Mexico for a simple news story, Superman ends up in a battle against the Aztec gods in this story by writer/artist Bef.

![SMTWORLD_1_POLAND_Preview(1).jpg](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/1743440398916-0S2WLM9G7RLLNHL32SE5/SMTWORLD_1_POLAND_Preview%281%29.jpg)

![SMTWORLD_1_POLAND_Preview(2).jpg](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/1743440396389-9TXAQIVPY2XJN98T4G4E/SMTWORLD_1_POLAND_Preview%282%29.jpg)

![SMTWORLD_1_POLAND_Preview(1).jpg](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/1743440398916-0S2WLM9G7RLLNHL32SE5/SMTWORLD_1_POLAND_Preview%281%29.jpg) ![SMTWORLD_1_POLAND_Preview(2).jpg](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/1743440396389-9TXAQIVPY2XJN98T4G4E/SMTWORLD_1_POLAND_Preview%282%29.jpg)

**“Marzanna,” by Bartosz Sztybor and Marek Oleksicki (Poland)**

Writer Sztybor and artist Oleksicki bring the Man of Steel to Warsaw, where an investigative assignment takes an unexpected turn. As Clark Kent delves into the local tradition of drowning the Marzanna effigy, he uncovers a chilling mystery tied to ancient legends and a looming threat over the city. In a race against time, Superman must confront forces beyond imagination to protect the people of Warsaw and prove that hope is the greatest power of all.

![SMTWORLD_1_SERBIA_dylux-1.jpg](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/1743440419202-M33A8MHBCM5P2CQLPA1V/SMTWORLD_1_SERBIA_dylux-1.jpg)

